            "source": "Benzinga",
            "source_type": "news",
            "summary": "Mandalay Resources Corporation reported its financial results for the fourth quarter and year ended December 31, 2024, showcasing significant growth and record revenue. In Q4 2024, the company generated $66.8 million in consolidated revenue, reflecting a 32% increase over Q4 2023. They achieved a consolidated cash operating cost of $1,085 per ounce of saleable gold equivalent production. Adjusted EBITDA saw a 40% increase to $32.3 million. Full-year 2024 revenue reached $240.7 million, a 39% surge from 2023, with consolidated cash cost of $1,106 per ounce. The company\u2019s net cash position stood at $76.4 million, up from $26.9 million in 2023. The CFO emphasized disciplined cost management and operational efficiencies that supported these achievements. For 2025, plans include advancing key investments in operations and exploration, with a focus on sustaining initiatives. The Company's audited consolidated financial statements and MD&A for 2024 are available on their website and www.sedarplus.ca.",
